INSERT INTO `claim_relationships` VALUES (1,7,11,'refines','Both critique LLM productivity research methodology. #7 identifies metric-level flaws (volume-based, self-reported). #11 identifies workflow-level flaws (conflating autocomplete with agentic). Complementary but distinct critiques.','2026-03-01 21:55:27'),(2,21,22,'generalizes','Claim 22 introduces the Lethal Trifecta framework within which claim 21 operates','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(3,22,25,'enables','Claim 22 identifies the problem condition (Lethal Trifecta) that claim 25 proposes to mitigate','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(4,25,26,'refines','Claim 26 (task decomposition) is one practical application of claim 25 (eliminating Trifecta legs)','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(5,22,27,'refines','Claim 27 refines claim 22 by noting that containers do not eliminate Lethal Trifecta risk','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(6,18,22,'refines','Claim 22 (Lethal Trifecta) provides structural definition of the attack condition described in claim 18','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(7,18,21,'refines','Claim 21 identifies prompt injection as a specific attack vector within the broader attack surface of claim 18','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(8,18,30,'refines','Claim 30 identifies internet access as a specific exfiltration mechanism within the broader risk of claim 18','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(9,30,32,'refines','Claim 32 (MCP write capabilities) refines claim 30 by identifying specific vectors for data exfiltration','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(10,26,31,'refines','Claim 31 (credential management) is a complementary mitigation pattern to claim 26 (task decomposition)','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(11,22,24,'depends_on','Claim 24 (browser extensions fatally flawed) assumes claim 22 (Lethal Trifecta) is present','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(12,21,23,'generalizes','Claim 23 generalizes claim 21 by asserting systemic lack of security across all agentic systems','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(13,26,28,'tensions_with','Claims 26 and 28 both address agentic risk through different mechanisms: technical (decomposition) vs. process (vetting)','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(14,26,29,'tensions_with','Claims 26 and 29 represent different responsibility models: technical mitigation vs. developer accountability','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(15,28,33,'refines','Claim 33 refines claim 28 by contextualizing the MCP Registry as a directory, not a security certification','2026-03-01 23:59:21'),(16,37,34,'refines','Claim 37 (no self-orchestration) is a specific architectural prohibition that instantiates claim 34 (structured conventions required). Claim 34 asserts the general principle; claim 37 identifies one specific failure mode to avoid.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(17,39,34,'refines','Claim 39 (specialized > generalist agents) is a specific design principle that instantiates claim 34 (structured conventions required). Specialization is one of the structures claim 34 argues for.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(18,45,34,'refines','Claim 45 (constraints > raw autonomy) is the adversarial restatement of claim 34. Claim 34 asserts what is needed; claim 45 asserts what is insufficient â€” they argue the same core position from different angles.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(19,39,37,'refines','Claim 39 (specialized single-responsibility agents) is a mechanism that avoids the problem claim 37 identifies. Replacing a self-orchestrating agent with a specialized network inherently removes meta-level self-control.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(20,35,34,'refines','Claim 35 (SDD with specs in repo) is the specific methodology that operationalizes claim 34 (structured conventions required). SDD is what those structured conventions look like in practice.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(21,42,35,'refines','Claim 42 (two-layer evaluation: deterministic checks + critic agent) is a specific component within the SDD pipeline described in claim 35. It refines SDD by specifying the quality-gate architecture.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(22,43,35,'refines','Claim 43 (knowledge agent for institutional memory) is a specific component within the SDD pipeline described in claim 35. It refines SDD by specifying how persistent project context is accumulated and maintained.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(23,46,36,'enables','Claim 46 (folder/naming conventions serve dual purpose) describes a structural mechanism that directly addresses the failure mode claim 36 identifies. Standardized conventions make decisions machine-readable and thus persistent across handoffs.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(24,38,41,'enables','Claim 38 (rule-based workflow engines) creates the deterministic, phase-gated substrate that makes claim 41 (inline evaluation at every stage) operationally feasible. Without deterministic phase transitions, there are no reliable stage boundaries at which to insert evaluation gates.','2026-03-02 00:38:41'),(25,47,7,'other','Parallel methodological caveats in different domains. Claim 7 critiques flawed AI productivity research; claim 47 notes that practitioner patterns on deterministic orchestration and agent specialization also lack quantitative validation. Both are epistemological warnings about the evidence base for claims in their respective topic areas. Flagged in claim 47 notes during decomposition.','2026-03-02 00:38:41');
